title: Approaches of domestic product (GDP)
maintainer_displayname: ZBO | Centraal Bureau voor de Statistiek
name: approaches-of-domestic-product-gdp
notes:
This table presents annual data on the output components, the final expenditure categories and the income components of gross domestic product of the Netherlands. In the national accounts gross domestic product is approached from three points of view: from the output, from the generation of income and from the final expenditure. Gross domestic product is a main macroeconomic indicator. The volume change of gross domestic product is a measure for the economic growth of a country.

The above mentioned macroeconomic variables are presented in:

- Value at current prices, mln euro
- Chainlinked volume value at prices reference year 2010, mln euro
- Volume changes, %
- Prices indices 2010=100

Data available from: 1995
Status of the figures:
The figures for the most recent reporting year 2013 are provisional. The figures for 2012 are revised provisional. The figures for 2011 are final.

All national accounts figures for 1995-2010 are provisional. This is because the revision of the national accounts has not been completed for the years before 2011. The revision, among other things, is needed to incorporate the European System of Accounts 2010. 

Changes as of September 24th 2014:
Data on the period 1995-2000 are added to the table. Furthermore, explanations and definitions are improved.

When will new figures be published?
Provisional, revised provisional and final data are published respectively 6, 18 en 30 months after the end of the reporting year.
